<p>I want to play audio which will be generated from a php script.</p>  <p>Client side:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;audio controls autoplay src="audio.php"&gt;&lt;/audio&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Server side:</p>  <pre><code>$path = 'somefile.mp3'; header('Content-Type: audio/mpeg'); header('Cache-Control: no-cache'); header("Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary"); readfile($path); </code></pre>  <p>It plays, but I can't change current the time in the audio element. The range slider is not working.</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/bPSiJ.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/bPSiJ.jpg" alt="Result"></a></p>